-- OpCapita Considering Sale of French Retailer But, Times Reports
-- B y   T h o m a s   B i e s h e u v e l
-- 2012-05-06T08:27:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-06/opcapita-considering-sale-of-french-retailer-but-times-reports.html
OpCapita LLP is considering a sale of
French furniture and electrical retailer But, the Sunday Times
reported, without saying how it obtained the information.  OpCapita bought the business for 550 million euros ($720
million) four years ago with  Goldman Sachs Group Inc. (GS)  and Colony
Capital LLC, the newspaper said.  OpCapita, Goldman Sachs and Colony Capital declined to
comment, the Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Biesheuvel in London at 
 tbiesheuvel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
